1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with gaze tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a novel learnable pooling module that can be trained end-to-end using backpropagation, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a method to improve the efficiency of gaze estimation using a learnable pooling module, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - Gaze tracking is an important technology in human-computer interaction, and the paper proposes a method to improve the accuracy and efficiency of gaze estimation. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with gaze tracking using a camera, which can be considered as a multimedia input.
